7 An Act relating to children; providing sunset;
creating the Teacher Recruitment and Retention
8 Program; directing that Program be administered by
Oklahoma Partnership for School Readiness; directing
9 promulgation of rules; providing income exemption for
certain individuals when determining eligibility for
10 child care subsidy program; directing provider to
provide certain notice to the Department of Human
11 Services; providing that all other conditions for
eligibility apply; directing the Department to waive
12 certain co-payment; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 461 of Title 10, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. 1. There is hereby created, until November 1, 2028, in
20 accordance with the Oklahoma Sunset Law, the Teacher Recruitment and
21 Retention Program to be administered by Oklahoma Partnership for
22 School Readiness under the direction of the Department of Human
23 Services.
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2778 Page 1
1 2. The Department of Human Services shall promulgate rules as
2 necessary to implement and enforce the provisions of this section,
3 including verifying income eligibility, employment status, and
4 administering subsidy benefits accordingly.
5 B. The Teacher Recruitment and Retention Program, administered
6 through Oklahoma Partnership for School Readiness, shall ensure
7 that:
8 1. A child care employee working at a child care facility
9 licensed pursuant to the Oklahoma Child Care Facilities Licensing
10 Act shall be eligible for the Teacher Recruitment and Retention
11 Program, provided that:
12 a. total annual gross household income does not exceed
13 One Hundred Twenty Thousand Dollars ($120,000.00) for
14 a two-parent household,
15 b. total annual gross household income does not exceed
16 Sixty Thousand Dollars ($60,000.00) for a single-
17 parent household, or
18 c. children must attend a program participating in the
19 Department of Human Services’ Child Care Subsidy
20 Program;
21 2. As used in this section, "child care employee" shall mean
22 any individual who is employed for a minimum of twenty (20) hours
23 per week, averaged monthly, who provides direct care, supervision or
24 educational services to children or who performs duties on-site that
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2778 Page 2
1 supp ort the daily operation of the facility participating in the
2 Child Care Subsidy Program and which is licensed pursuant to the
3 Oklahoma Child Care Facilities Licensing Act;
4 3. An employee who qualifies under the household income
5 limitations in paragraph 1 of this subsection:
6 a. shall have household income exempted from
7 consideration solely for purposes of calculating cost-
8 sharing or co-payment responsibilities,
9 b. shall have co-payments waived if eligible under the
10 Department’s Child Care Subsidy Program, and
11 c. shall be eligible to participate in the Teacher
12 Recruitment and Retention Program, even if his or her
13 income exceeds the Child Care Subsidy Program
14 requirements;
15 4. When an employee who is employed by a licensed child care
16 facility leaves employment of the licensed provider, the provider
17 shall provide written notice within thirty (30) days to the
18 Department of Human Services that the employee is no longer
19 employed; and
20 5. Other than the income exemption pursuant to paragraph 1 of
21 this subsection and the reporting requirements established pursuant
22 to this subsection, all other conditions of eligibility for the
23 Child Care Subsidy Program located in Oklahoma Administrative Code
24 (OAC) 340:40-7-1 shall be followed.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2778 Page 3
1 C. Subsection B of this section shall not apply to employees
2 who are employed by a child care facility licensed pursuant to the
3 Oklahoma Child Care Facilities Licensing Act and who are eligible
4 for the Child Care Subsidy Program without household income being
5 exempted.
6 D. The Department of Human Services shall waive co-payments for
7 employees who are employed by a licensed child care facility and who
8 qualify under income eligibility requirements of the Child Care
9 Subsidy Program.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
11 Passed the House of Representatives the 20th day of May, 2025.
